About.Name: Francesco De Lorenzo
About.AboutText:
Hi I am Francesco De Lorenzo Im a junior in electrical engineering. Currently, I am pursuing my undergraduate degree at Seattle Pacific University. I am dedicated to expanding my knowledge and skills in various areas of Electrical Engineering, with a particular focus on circuitry and R&D. I thrive in collaborative environments where I can contribute my expertise and learn from my peers.

I believe in the importance of continuous learning and seek out opportunities to explore new technologies and methodologies.

Project1.Title: Bandpass Sallen Key IR Detector
Project1.Desc: This is the assembled circuit on a breaboard which successfully filters out all prequencies but 10kHz, then using a peak detector will find the peak voltage and run that into a comparator to signal an LED to turn on when the correct frequency is passed.
